Gather together with each other.

32
00:02:19.890 --> 00:02:21.945
That's a worthy cause.

33
00:02:25.543 --> 00:02:28.830
Right, let's focus on the duh sound.

34
00:02:29.960 --> 00:02:32.310
To pronounce the duh sound.

35
00:02:32.310 --> 00:02:35.770
You place your tongue slightly
different from the th sound.

36
00:02:35.770 --> 00:02:40.730
You have to feel your tongue pushing
against the area where your upper teeth

37
00:02:40.730 --> 00:02:43.120
and the roof of your mouth meet.

38
00:02:43.120 --> 00:02:44.610
You push quite hard so

39
00:02:44.610 --> 00:02:49.610
no air can get out of your mouth
while you vibrate your vocal cords.

40
00:02:49.610 --> 00:02:51.466
This build pressure in your mouth.

41
00:02:51.466 --> 00:02:56.510
The sound duh is made by
suddenly releasing your tongue so

42
00:02:56.510 --> 00:02:59.670
that it touches your lower
teeth at the end of the sound.

43
00:03:00.870 --> 00:03:05.850
There should be a distinct duh
created as you make the sound.

